          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">Bucket-wheel excavators mine rare earth materials in the Zhytomyr region of Ukraine. Credits: Kostiantyn Liberov/Libkos/Getty Images</p>
        </mj-text> 

        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
         
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Ukrainian PM Denys Shmyhal said Ukraine and the US had finalized a version of the agreement on Ukrainian minerals. President Volodymyr Zelenskyy stated that the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-27-02-2025-h1-2-us-has-not-offered-any-specific-security-guarantees?source=website" target="_blank">United States has not offered specific security guarantees</a> for Ukraine in exchange for its natural resources. The agreement will be discussed during his visit to Washington on Friday.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;filter:blur(5px);">Trump has affirmed that providing security is Europe’s responsibility. He also wrote off the possibility of Ukraine joining NATO. The US president stressed that Ukraine’s NATO aspirations were the root cause of the war. While Trump pledged to end the war, Zelenskyy said the war will not end without security guarantees. 
       </p>
        </mj-text>
